						<div class="postbody">Yeah, Atari programmers are like the Ancient Gods of game programming. Anybody who can pull off a <em>Battlezone</em> or <em>Moon Patrol</em> (WITH parallax scrolling intact!) on that hardware is more than human.
<br />
<br />Anyway, those graphics are middling for 2600. Not quite <em>Battlezone</em> nice, but certainly better than <em>Boxing</em> or other early titles. I'd guess that's due to one of two things: programmer inexperience with the Atari (hardly surprising, as very few people homebrew for it) or lack of CPU time/memory to do nice graphics (also not surprising when you consider how much stuff is going on at once in <em>Mega Man.</em>)</div>

					
